1514.question: How much performance improvements they achieve on SQuAD?

6-Table2-1.png: The table shows the performance of different models on the SQuAD dataset. The performance is measured in terms of F1 score, which is a harmonic mean of precision and recall. The table shows that the SAN model achieves the highest F1 score of 0.81, followed by the BDA/Self-Attention + MoPeters et al. (2016) model with an F1 score of 0.79. The RN model achieves the lowest F1 score of 0.61.

1514.answer: Compared to baselines SAN (Table 1) shows  improvement of 1.096% on EM and 0.689% F1. Compared to other published SQuAD results (Table 2) SAN is ranked second.
